  "text": "Though the Wave Form Capture (WFC) on GEOTAIL operates only 8.7 s every 5 min [CITATION_1] , we do have the data from the WFC at critical periods when the 3-D transient magnetic reconnection took place near the spacecraft at the dayside magnetopause boundary layer. We observed a variety of waveforms in this reconnection event [CITATION_2] . One of the interesting waveforms is for the Electrostatic Solitary Waves (ESWs), a series of large amplitude electric bipolar pulses parallel to the local magnetic field, which is shown at the top of Fig. 2 .",
